{"talk":{"id":32015,"name":"Karl Skjonnemand: The self-assembling computer chips of the future","description":"The transistors that power the phone in your pocket are unimaginably small: you can fit more than 3,000 of them across the width of a human hair. But to keep up with innovations in fields like facial recognition and augmented reality, we need to pack even more computing power into our computer chips -- and we're running out of space. In this forward-thinking talk, technology developer Karl Skjonnemand introduces a radically new way to create chips. \"This could be the dawn of a new era of molecular manufacturing,\" Skjonnemand says.","slug":"karl_skjonnemand_the_self_assembling_computer_chips_of_the_future","recorded_at":"2018-11-26 00:00:00","published_at":"2019-02-27 15:38:31","updated_at":"2020-09-28 21:42:15","viewed_count":937143,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":476,"name":"TED@Merck KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3a37f7c29ba824eed1626c4c45ff9d0dc6a644d7_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3a37f7c29ba824eed1626c4c45ff9d0dc6a644d7_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3a37f7c29ba824eed1626c4c45ff9d0dc6a644d7_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/3a37f7c29ba824eed1626c4c45ff9d0dc6a644d7_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/28ec76264af5dc48fe8b5b0ab5fcc62a38a91fc0_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/KarlSkjonnemand_2018S-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":5920891,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/KarlSkjonnemand_2018S-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":16377182,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks